Fig. 
25

) subquadrate, dark brown, with large pale areas medially; lateral margins incompletely fringed. Mesonotum and metanotum nearly similar in size, yellow-brown, with various darker markings. Thoracic gill tufts consisting of nine pairs: two on posterior supracoxal prosternum (PSC 
1
, sensu 

