), and one on anterior thoracic metasternum (AT 
3
). Legs relatively long, somewhat flattened; femora fringed with stout brown setae on both anterior and posterior regions (medially bare), with row of long white hairs along posterior margin; tibiae relatively long, slender, fringed with dense white hairs along outer margin.

Egg. Egg (
Fig. 24
) oval, ca. 0.30 mm long and 0.21 mm wide; both poles similar. Collar and anchor absent. Chorion completely thin and seemingly smooth. Micropyles in upper third; orifices sessile.
